719958f-a.title: Manhattan: Fulton Street - Nassau Street
719958f-a.text:
Fulton Street, west from Nassau Street, across Broadway, to Church
Street, showing between the latter two points the Cemetery of St. Pauls
P.E. Chapel. The structure,with a flag atop.is the N.Y. Telephone
Building, No. 140 West Street. This view is taken westward from the
15-story Dowling Building, No. 10B Fulton Street, south side, between
Dutch and William Streets.
June 30, 1928.
P. L. Sperr.
